                <h2 data-uuid="ad870ba6f39f4b61a5a91984e4212941"> Document-Based Investigation</h2>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="f9b443227b86428c97496466dd4b24f1">Part 2: Write
                an Analytical Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="d39c0e5537484666899b48c8eec3ff7e">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="ff8e293b46a041c4a38b0c7f56d64936">As Europeans colonized the Americas in the 1500s
                and 1600s, they developed economies that required a lot of labor, mostly for
                work in mines and on plantations. To meet the need for labor, colonists imported
                Africans, whom they forced to work on their plantations. Slavery was accepted
                throughout the early English colonies of North America. By the early 1800s,
                however, slavery disappeared in the northern United States, even as the
                institution strengthened in the South. By the middle of the century, the nation
                was deeply divided over the issue of slavery.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="bf553c28c208422789ef4790f1d12670">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="46aeb38a1c2d44379af92ee832f811e9"></p>
            <p data-uuid="ece1dddc8e2642e7bee486af6575dcc7">What was it like to live in and resist the slave system? How
                did different groups of people resist slavery? Write an analytical essay in
                which you examine the slave system, the reasons people resisted it, and the forms
                of resistance that people used.</p>
            <p data-uuid="facfd618cb104b0f987ba1921f55ae01">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose
                your analytical essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="a784ce6d8d88410295368c5f9050d9d0">
                <li data-uuid="1ac12174ff544366acb702590b4c4102">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="ca204596703a4a738190621438dadcf5">Use at least <i>three</i> of the
                    sources in Part 1, and develop the topic with relevant, well-chosen text
                    evidence from the documents.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="4a2c363928784c9f8acca5c5d617bf96">
                    Cite specific text evidence from each of the sources in your response.</li>
                <li data-uuid="96195895f1c74aceb113178bc6fea2c2">
                    Plan your analytical essay so that it includes an
                    introduction, body paragraphs with supporting details, and a concluding
                    paragraph.</li>
                <li data-uuid="246bc2d03c2a407aaec1ea7987711314">Organize your essay in a clear and logical way that
                    links your details to the topic.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="a3d5c1fc05314986b1088a22f34b599f">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and
                    supports the information you present.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
